  "body": "Most of the time we will something like `{this.props.children.map(this.renderChild)}` for render the children in some component because we need to clone the element or do something with it.\n\nRight now I am facing a problem because when I pass just a child the `map` function is no longer there because is an object so we will end on something like this all the time, creating a little layer for deal with this problem.\n\nMaybe we can take the approach of always create a array even when you pass a single element unless you see a problem there.\n\n``` js\nreturn (\n  <div>\n    {this.renderChildren()}\n  </div>\n)\n\n...\n\nrenderChildren() {\n  if(Array.isArray(this.props.children)) {\n    return this.props.children.map(this.renderChild)\n  }\n\n  return this.renderChild(this.props.children, 0)\n}\n```\n",
